\subsection{Wreath product}
\begin{definition}\label{group.wreath_product}
\uses{group,group.semidirect_product}
If $S\leq S_n$ and $H$ are {{KNOWL('group', 'groups')}}, the **wreath product** of $H$ and $S$ is the {{KNOWL('group.semidirect_product', 'semidirect product')}} $$H \wr S = H^n \rtimes S$$
where $S$ acts on $H^n$ via $S\subseteq S_n$, permuting the $n$ copies of $H$.

If $S$ is a transitive subgroup of $S_n$, we say that the wreath product is **transitive**.
\end{definition}


